mainBoard.flavorText: On guard for larger dangers, we underestimated the power and speed of the Imp's muck-crusted claws.

mainBoard.flavorText: The only sound was the gentle clicking of the Faeries' wings. Then those intruders who were still standing turned and fled. One thing was certain: they didn't think the Scryb were very funny anymore.
mainBoard.name: Scryb Sprites

mainBoard.flavorText: Don't try to outrun one of Dominia's Grizzlies; it'll catch you, knock you down, and eat you. Of course, you could run up a tree. In that case you'll get a nice view before it knocks the tree down and eats you.
mainBoard.name: Grizzly Bears

mainBoard.flavorText:
"'Do you know, I always thought Unicorns were fabulous monsters, too? I never saw one alive before!' 'Well, now that we *have* seen each other,' said the Unicorn, 'if you'll believe in me, I'll believe in you.'"
—Lewis Carroll
